The availability of transport from France to the UK is subject to change. The availability of transport may reduce further. If youâ€™re travelling in France and wish to return to the UK, you should make travel plans to do so as soon as possible. Contact your travel operator and check the website of your airline or ferry company further advice before you travel.
Cross-Channel train and ferry services continue to operate but with some services being severely reduced.
Flights to the UK continue, however some airlines are severely reducing their services. From midday 17 March, flights departing from French airports may be cancelled or rescheduled. You should check with your airline for the latest information.
